National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan had a phone conversation with Croatian Prime Minister Andrej Plenkovic. Sullivan expressed the Biden Administration's gratitude for the strong relationship between the United States and Croatia and emphasized their commitment to strengthening transatlantic ties. He also congratulated the Prime Minister on Croatia's recent opening of the KrK Island liquefied natural gas terminal and its progress in meeting the requirements to join the U.S. Visa Waiver Program. The discussion also covered coordination on shared priorities such as the COVID-19 pandemic, energy diversification, and the Western Balkans.